===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|belle}}, from {{inh|en|ang|belle||bell}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*bellǭ}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|belle}}, {{m|fy|bel}}, {{cog|nl|bel}}, {{cog|nds|Belle}}, {{m|nds|Bel}}, {{cog|da|bjelde}}, {{cog|sv|bjällra}}, {{cog|no|bjelle}}, {{cog|is|bjalla}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A percussive instrument made of metal or other hard material, typically but not always in the shape of an inverted cup with a flared rim, which [[resonate]]s when struck.
#* '''1848''', {{w|Edgar Allan Poe}}, "{{w|The Bells}}"
#*: ''HEAR the sledges with the '''bells''' &mdash;''
#*: ''Silver '''bells'''!''
#*: ''What a world of merriment their melody foretells!''
# The sounding of a bell as a signal.
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=December 18, 2011| author=Ben Dirs| title=Carl Froch outclassed by dazzling Andre Ward| work=BBC Sport| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/boxing/16234673.stm| passage=Referee Steve Smoger was an almost invisible presence in the ring as both men went at it, although he did have a word with Froch when he landed with a shot after the '''bell''' at the end of the eighth.}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly|British|informal}} A [[telephone call]].
#: ''I’ll give you a '''bell''' later.''
# A signal at a [[school]] that tells the students when a class is starting or ending.
# {{lb|en|music}} The [[flared]] [[end]] of a [[brass]] or [[woodwind]] instrument.
# {{lb|en|nautical}} Any of a series of [[stroke]]s on a bell (or similar), struck every half hour to indicate the [[time]] (within a four hour watch)
# The flared end of a [[pipe]], designed to mate with a narrow [[spigot]].
# {{lb|en|computing}} A [[device]] [[control code]] that produces a [[beep]] (or rings a small electromechanical bell on older [[teleprinter]]s etc.).
# Anything shaped like a bell, such as the cup or corolla of a flower.
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Tempest|V|i|passage=In a cowslip's '''bell''' I lie.}}
# {{lb|en|architecture}} The part of the [[capital]] of a [[column]] included between the [[abacus]] and neck molding; also used for the naked core of nearly cylindrical shape, assumed to exist within the [[leafage]] of a capital.
# An instrument situated on a [[bicycle]]'s [[handlebar]], used by the [[cyclist]] to warn of his or her presence.

